long-description.p:
Dublin Airport is Ireland's biggest airport by with annual passengers of around 20 million.
The airport caters for a wide range of operators both long haul european carriers daily services include Aer Lingus, American Airlines, Delta Airlines & Continental Airlines.
Low cost flights from the airport are of course Ryanair which has its own hub.
The airport offers a number of great vantage points for plane spotters this being one of them.
The cache is a micro sized container please rehide it carefully to prevent muggles from discovering its location.

ul.li:
2010-05-29T19:00:00Z : Found it by lochb
Quick find after I'd picked up the hire car to drive to Limerick. Lots of rather vocal cows here! My first find in Ireland. TFTC and G'Day from Australia!

2010-05-08T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
This was a 'Windsockers' themed day of cache finds around the airport. This was #2 of 7.
SL TFTC

2010-04-18T19:00:00Z : Found it by dsquaredd2
Lots of grounded birds, none moving. Very sad for one trying to get home. Fourth and last of a long (about 5 mile round trip) to grab several caches surrounding the airport. Starting in sunshine, ending in darkness. This is when I realized I had to go back the way I came, bummer. TFTC!

2010-04-06T19:00:00Z : Found it by Sean O'Neill
17:32 Hrs,#1693. TNLNSL TFTC

2010-04-01T19:00:00Z : Found it by Moonshiner Extraordinaire
I had tried to find this cache twice before – I didn’t even get to the co-ordinates on 09/02/2009 (note) and a DNF on 23/05/2009 (cache was gone). Today was a bit of an anti-climax – I parked just a few metres away, walked to GPS ‘0’, looked – and there it was. Found at 15:55, just 1 metre from ‘0’. Back to the car to sign the log – then had to wait for a muggle-free moment (that’s a busy road) to replace the cache. Gazillions of Aer Lingus planes came and went. Go raibh maith agat faoi’n taisce.
Moonshiner X (cache #1,257)
